====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To put together with a seam.
# To make the appearance of a seam in, as in knitting a stocking; hence, to knit with a certain stitch, like that in such knitting.
# To mark with a seam or line; to [[scar]].
#* {{rfdate||and other bibliographic particulars}} {{w|Alexander Pope}}
#*: '''Seamed''' o'er with wounds which his own sabre gave.
# To crack open along a seam.
#* {{rfdate||and other bibliographic particulars}} {{w|L. Wallace}}
#*: Later their lips began to parch and '''seam'''.
# {{lb|en|cricket}} Of the ball, to move sideways after bouncing on the seam.
# {{lb|en|cricket}} Of a bowler, to make the ball move thus.

